#The Important Facts

Canada officially became a country in 1867. At that time, it is well known that Sir John A. MacDonald was a very, very drunk man who once let the Canadian Pacific Railroad influence his political decisions.

## Other Super Important Facts

To be competent in school, you must accomplish a number of important tasks:

1. Wake up on time.
2. Be awake at least 56% of the time.
3. Don't not be awake at least 56% of the time.
4. Invest in a good coffee machine.
5. Pray to the deity of your choice as much as possible, because they will not be able to save you from this slow descent into madness.
6. Dress for the part.
7. Brush your teeth, please.

Most importantly, also do the work for your courses.
